New Records: South Africa's centuries by Quinton de Kock (114) and Rassie van der Dussen (133) were their highest individual scores in the tournament.
South Africa's total of 357-4 was their highest score in the World Cup 2023 so far.
Key Match Events: South Africa's 190-run victory over New Zealand was their sixth win of the tournament.
Quinton de Kock and Rassie van der Dussen's 200-run partnership was the highest fourth-wicket partnership in the World Cup 2023.
Marco Jansen's four-wicket haul and Gerald Coetzee's two-wicket contribution were key bowling performances.
Pre-Game Insights: The match was anticipated following South Africa's recent clash with New Zealand in the Rugby World Cup final.
South Africa's batting strategy focused on building partnerships after their previous high-scoring match.
Post-Match Reflections: South Africa captain Temba Bavuma praised the team's clinical performance with both bat and ball.
New Zealand captain Tom Latham acknowledged the pressure caused by South Africa's opening partnership and the loss of key bowler Matt Henry.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The win moved South Africa ahead of India in the World Cup 2023 standings.
New Zealand's batting struggles and injuries, including Devon Edgell's injury, impacted their performance.
